# Prompt 3 / task-runtime agent constraints

When continuing NexusRBX Prompt 3 (task runtime, Studio transport, agent orchestration):

## Authority

- Prompt 1 docs in `docs/architecture-audit-2026-07-18/` are canonical contracts.
- Prompt 2 asset platform remains adapter-owned; do not redesign schemas or the icon generator.
- Prompt 3 docs in `docs/task-runtime-2026-07-19/` govern runtime, flags, and gates.
- Preserve all existing dirty worktree changes. Do not restart or rewrite the programme.

## Non-negotiables

- The model is not the task runtime. Durable state, idempotency, retries, and verification live in application code.
- Queue / ACK / delivery is never completion. `succeeded` requires trusted verification evidence.
- Exactly one runtime owns side effects. Dual mode means mirrored records, never dual execution.
- Every external write needs a durable operation ID and idempotency key; ambiguous outcomes stay `outcome_unknown` until reconciled.
- New routes, Studio envelope v2, Prompt 2 writes, and Roblox mutations stay default-off until staged gates pass.
- Master Roblox upload consent cannot be overridden by request or project toggles.

## Working style

- Search and read before editing. Prefer extending existing owners (`artifactRunLauncher`, Studio bridge, asset services, job worker) over parallel systems.
- Keep changes surgical. No unrelated refactors, docs spam, or flag enablement “to finish.”
- Do not claim production-ready or verified completion without evidence from the verification docs and live gates.
- Prefer typed errors and fail-closed behavior over optimistic success paths.

